    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Is there any practical way to do this only when we're running in the kernel? In the terminal, it would be useful to keep Ctrl-C working the way it normally does (i.e. new prompt within pdb).\n\nThis is specifically an issue in the notebook - you can't run into the problem in a console-style interface. But by design we can't distinguish different frontends in the kernel.\n"
  },
