    "created_at": "2014-05-02T20:31:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-02T20:31:29Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm generally not as averse to configurability as @ellisonbg, but in this case I don't think it's worth making it configurable. It would only add complexity to a get around having to type `%debug` to get back into pdb if one accidentally `Ctrl-C` and pops out of there after this is merged. On the other hand, this solves a real problem that's much harder to get out of - a wedged kernel that must be restarted if the client which initiated the session loses the handle on it (by either re-executing the cell and losing the output block, or reloading the page). So let's merge this as is.\n"
  },
